Create Date Table, Data Model, Calculated Column and Measures in the Power BI desktop model 9


Go to data view after data load.

Click on new table tab in the ribbon.

Copy and paste the code below in the code editor:


Date Table =  ADDCOLUMNS(
                                                                 CALENDAR (
                                                                                                  DATE ( YEAR ( MIN('lending_club_loans'[issue date])),6,1),
                                                                                                  DATE ( YEAR (MAX ('lending_club_loans'[issue date])),12,1)
                                                                                                  ),
                                                     "Year", YEAR ([Date]),
                        "Month", FORMAT ([Date], "MM" ),
 "MonthNameShort", FORMAT ( [Date],"mmm" )
                                                                            )

Right click on the date table and select mark as date. (See the gif)


1. Creating Date Table

Go to report view, in the home tab, click on Enter Data button.




2. Create Data Model

Go to Model view, establish relationship between the source table and the date table as shown in the gif.



3. Create Column



In Data view, go to the home tab, click on new column button and paste the code below in the code editor:


Total_Recovery Amt = [collection_recovery_fee]+ lending_club_loans[total_rec_late_fee]


4. Create Measure


Create a Measure table that will accommodate all the measures and hide the column 1. Kindly follow the gif below



Create the measures  by clicking on the Measure button in the report view.

Paste each of the codes below in the code editor:

1.  Number of Loans = COUNTX(lending_club_loans,'lending_club_loans'[funded_amnt])

2. Total_Recoveries = SUM('lending_club_loans'[Total_Recovery Amt])



3. TOTAL_PROFIT =
VAR TOTAL_REC_INT = SUM(lending_club_loans[total_rec_int])
VAR TOTAL_RECOVERIES = SUM(lending_club_loans[Total_Recovery Amt])
RETURN
TOTAL_RECOVERIES + TOTAL_REC_INT



4.PROFIT_PER_LOAN = IF (
CALCULATE(
DIVIDE([TOTAL_PROFIT],[Number of Loans])) = BLANK(),
0,
IF (
CALCULATE(
DIVIDE([TOTAL_PROFIT],[Number of Loans])) <> BLANK(),
CALCULATE(
DIVIDE([TOTAL_PROFIT], [Number of Loans])
)
)
)



6. Total_Out_Loan = CALCULATE( SUM(lending_club_loans[out_prncp]),
VALUES('lending_club_loans'[loan_status])
)



7.  Net charge_off =
VAR TotalPrincipal_Rec = SUM('lending_club_loans'[total_rec_prncp]) --HERE I SUM THE COL
VAR CHARGE_OFF_GROSS = CALCULATE (TotalPrincipal_Rec, --ITERATE THROUGH THIS TABLE AND RETURN VALUES WHERE
FILTER(ALL('lending_club_loans'[loan_status] ),--I FILTER THE Loan_status for
'lending_club_loans'[loan_status] IN {( "Charged Off"), --THIS QUALITY AND
( "Does not meet the credit policy. Status:Charged Off") --THIS QUALITY
}
))
VAR RECOVERIES = SUM('lending_club_loans'[Total_Recovery Amt]) --SUM ALL
VAR DIFFERENCE = (CHARGE_OFF_GROSS - RECOVERIES ) --SUBTRACT ALL RECOVERIES FROM GROSS CHARGE-OFF RETURN DIFFERENCE
VAR LOAN_OUTSTANDING = SUM('lending_club_loans'[out_prncp])
VAR NET = DIVIDE(DIFFERENCE,LOAN_OUTSTANDING,0)/100 RETURN NET/100


8. PY PROFIT_PER_LOAN = CALCULATE(
[PROFIT_PER_LOAN], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR('Date Table'[Date])
)


9. YOY PROFIT_PER_LOAN = DIVIDE([PROFIT_PER_LOAN] - [PY PROFIT_PER_LOAN],
[PY PROFIT_PER_LOAN])


10. KPIArrow_YoY Profit per loan = (SWITCH(true(),
[YOY PROFIT_PER_LOAN] < 0 ,UNICHAR(129055),
[YOY PROFIT_PER_LOAN] > 0 ,UNICHAR(129053))
)

11.Blank = ""
